modules.description: This module implements an in-memory file system with operations for creating, reading, writing, and managing files and directories. It supports data types like `Cstruct.t` for binary data and `string` paths, with functions to handle file metadata, directory listings, and structural modifications. Concrete use cases include simulating file storage in test environments and managing ephemeral data in networked applications.

This module implements an in-memory file system with operations to create, read, write, and manage files and directories. It works with `Cstruct.t` for binary data and `string` paths, supporting file metadata, directory listings, and structural modifications. Use it to simulate file storage in test environments or manage ephemeral data in networked applications.
